1
00:00:17,607 --> 00:00:18,047
Flamme?

2
00:00:18,848 --> 00:00:19,689
You mean Master.

3
00:00:22,331 --> 00:00:22,751
What is it?

4
00:00:23,912 --> 00:00:26,354
Do you really think the way
you dealt with them was unfair?

5
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:32,858
Frieren, do you remember Basalt's
final words before he perished?

6
00:00:34,600 --> 00:00:35,480
Why would I bother?

7
00:00:36,521 --> 00:00:38,503
Their kind only uses
words to deceive.

8
00:00:40,204 --> 00:00:40,884
Smart girl.

9
00:00:41,485 --> 00:00:44,467
They are nothing more than monsters
that can imitate the human tongue.

10
00:00:45,218 --> 00:00:49,262
I call them demons, and take it
from an expert, they are all the same.

11
00:00:50,843 --> 00:00:55,647
They don't play fair, so we have no choice
but to take their lead and deceive doubly so.

12
00:00:57,189 --> 00:01:02,974
If this could be the secret to exterminating their species,
then I will gladly embrace the dishonor it entails.

13
00:02:45,119 --> 00:02:46,159
The bleeding won't stop.

14
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:48,720
This is the end.

15
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:52,061
It would seem your plan
has failed rather badly.

16
00:02:53,842 --> 00:02:54,702
Yes, perhaps.

17
00:02:55,322 --> 00:02:57,743
But Frieren won't
make it out unscathed.

18
00:02:58,863 --> 00:03:02,964
By this hour, I'm sure she and
Lady Aura have begun to clash.

19
00:03:04,185 --> 00:03:07,666
Decades ago, we were forced
to retreat by the Party of Heroes.

20
00:03:08,426 --> 00:03:11,207
But this time, she has
no heroes to hide behind.

21
00:03:12,715 --> 00:03:18,617
I do admit your ally poses a threat to
us, but her mana is no match for my lady's.

22
00:03:19,657 --> 00:03:23,318
If Frieren attacks her head on,
she'll most certainly lose the fight.

23
00:03:24,138 --> 00:03:27,019
In that case, I have no
doubt my mistress will win.

24
00:03:28,199 --> 00:03:32,080
She would never directly engage a demon,
especially not one that's so powerful.

25
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:34,801
She'll kill Aura
by tricking her.

26
00:03:36,821 --> 00:03:37,441
Nonsense.

27
00:03:38,122 --> 00:03:39,162
I know this mage.

28
00:03:40,232 --> 00:03:43,554
Frieren the Slayer has never
once fought us from the shadows.

29
00:03:45,335 --> 00:03:47,657
Why then do I feel
something is wrong?

30
00:03:50,018 --> 00:03:51,920
This girl's mana is weak.

31
00:03:52,940 --> 00:03:56,402
Yet I was overwhelmed by the
sheer number of her rapid attacks.

32
00:03:58,003 --> 00:04:02,186
How was she able to execute such
powerful magic without exhausting her mana?

33
00:04:04,608 --> 00:04:05,148
I see.

34
00:04:06,209 --> 00:04:07,790
Is such a thing even possible?

35
00:04:09,617 --> 00:04:11,137
So Frieren does the same?

36
00:04:12,458 --> 00:04:13,778
Too afraid to fight fair?

37
00:04:15,079 --> 00:04:18,300
Both you and your teacher are
a disgrace to the title of mage.

38
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:26,142
I assure you Mistress Frieren
knows that better than anyone else.

39
00:04:32,444 --> 00:04:33,884
What horrors await today?

40
00:04:35,765 --> 00:04:37,205
This is an Elven village.

41
00:04:49,916 --> 00:04:50,977
Basalt the Throne.

42
00:04:51,838 --> 00:04:53,579
A general of the
Demon King's army.

43
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:57,082
He must have led his forces
here to destroy this town.

44
00:05:00,545 --> 00:05:01,445
Speak up, girl.

45
00:05:01,526 --> 00:05:02,666
Was it you who killed him?

46
00:05:03,247 --> 00:05:04,508
You look near dead yourself.

47
00:05:11,173 --> 00:05:12,815
Good bit of mana you have there.

48
00:05:13,435 --> 00:05:14,356
You must be powerful.

49
00:05:15,137 --> 00:05:16,578
You took them
head on, didn't you?

50
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:21,431
A brute in disguise.

51
00:05:21,691 --> 00:05:22,852
That was a foolish mistake.

52
00:05:23,772 --> 00:05:26,434
I don't know why people
prefer an honest playing field.

53
00:05:26,895 --> 00:05:29,036
Run or hide, or take
them by surprise.

54
00:05:29,336 --> 00:05:31,678
You're working both
safer and smarter if you do.

55
00:05:31,698 --> 00:05:34,840
I can't understand the
way strong mages think.

56
00:05:36,361 --> 00:05:37,102
Well, you should.

57
00:05:38,743 --> 00:05:39,003
Huh?

58
00:05:40,084 --> 00:05:42,165
You should understand
exactly how I think.

59
00:05:45,487 --> 00:05:49,530
I'm certain you are far
more powerful a mage than I.

60
00:06:00,778 --> 00:06:02,019
And what makes you say that?

61
00:06:04,081 --> 00:06:04,881
Call it a hunch.

62
00:06:07,344 --> 00:06:07,964
Interesting.

63
00:06:08,885 --> 00:06:09,385
Have a name?

64
00:06:13,949 --> 00:06:15,210
What happened to the village?

65
00:06:16,211 --> 00:06:17,152
Its people are dead.

66
00:06:17,612 --> 00:06:19,514
Not even the women
and children were spared.

67
00:06:21,389 --> 00:06:22,349
I couldn't save them.

68
00:06:23,110 --> 00:06:25,251
Being their strongest
didn't do me any good.

69
00:06:25,991 --> 00:06:27,872
Trying to save
them at all was silly.

70
00:06:28,172 --> 00:06:31,313
If it were me, one side of those
monsters would have sent me for the hills.

71
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:33,554
Put me down.

72
00:06:34,174 --> 00:06:34,414
No.

73
00:06:35,314 --> 00:06:36,175
You have potential.

74
00:06:37,035 --> 00:06:38,256
You're going to
be my apprentice.

75
00:06:40,256 --> 00:06:41,697
Don't forget I saved your life.

76
00:06:42,442 --> 00:06:45,504
If I hadn't shown up, you would
be sharing a grave with that demon.

77
00:06:46,024 --> 00:06:48,485
You failed to protect your
village and nearly yourself.

78
00:06:48,745 --> 00:06:49,926
You would have died in vain.

79
00:06:50,626 --> 00:06:52,487
But luckily, I was
there to assist.

80
00:06:55,769 --> 00:06:56,329
Behind us.

81
00:06:58,130 --> 00:07:00,011
These are stronger than
the general you killed.

82
00:07:07,935 --> 00:07:09,676
Fascinating
creatures, aren't they?

83
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:15,056
They fully intended to catch us off guard by
concealing their mana until just before they struck.

84
00:07:15,837 --> 00:07:21,160
But the moment they realized we were mages,
they waltzed out into the open with grandeur.

85
00:07:22,181 --> 00:07:24,102
They are cunning and
they never play fair.

86
00:07:24,702 --> 00:07:28,465
But every last one of them has a ridiculous
sense of pride when it comes to magic.

87
00:07:30,206 --> 00:07:31,927
You may leave, human mage.

88
00:07:32,588 --> 00:07:34,609
Once you put down
the elf girl, that is.

89
00:07:35,609 --> 00:07:37,791
And you'll let me go
free if I do as you say.

90
00:07:38,318 --> 00:07:39,499
Massacre the elves.

91
00:07:39,939 --> 00:07:40,319
Now.

92
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:42,801
Those were the
Demon King's orders.

93
00:07:43,401 --> 00:07:45,803
Your existence
matters not to me.

94
00:07:46,703 --> 00:07:47,524
How thoughtful.

95
00:07:52,247 --> 00:07:54,789
Frieren, you were right before.

96
00:07:55,469 --> 00:07:58,071
I'm painfully aware of how
a powerful mage thinks.

97
00:07:59,432 --> 00:08:02,093
Much like I'm aware of
how these creatures think.

98
00:08:03,154 --> 00:08:07,717
I know the absolute faith they have in these
magics they've poured their lives into studying.

99
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:13,021
In other words, I know they're an
arrogant and overconfident breed.

100
00:08:27,304 --> 00:08:31,645
Frieren, they lacked your perception
and quickly judged me a weakling.

101
00:08:33,777 --> 00:08:39,121
Though I admit they were exceptional mages,
their overconfidence cost them their lives.

102
00:08:40,282 --> 00:08:45,106
By controlling the release of your mana, you hid
your strength so they didn't see you as a threat.

103
00:08:46,708 --> 00:08:47,188
That's right.

104
00:08:48,309 --> 00:08:52,152
I deceive and kill my enemies by
allowing them to miscalculate my power.

105
00:08:53,413 --> 00:08:58,237
It is a cowardly and unfair way to fight that
makes a mockery of the art of magic itself.

106
00:09:14,547 --> 00:09:16,128
Your injuries are
looking much better.

107
00:09:19,451 --> 00:09:21,353
I'd say it's time we
begin your training.

108
00:09:23,675 --> 00:09:24,076
Flamme?

109
00:09:24,796 --> 00:09:25,717
You mean Master.

110
00:09:30,602 --> 00:09:33,104
The demons took all that
I've ever known from me.

111
00:09:33,804 --> 00:09:34,265
Me too.

112
00:09:35,686 --> 00:09:37,688
I wish to eradicate
every last one.

113
00:09:39,149 --> 00:09:39,610
Me too.

114
00:09:41,192 --> 00:09:43,734
But I love magic and
hold great respect for it.

115
00:09:44,034 --> 00:09:45,134
You and I are the same.

116
00:09:47,996 --> 00:09:50,798
That's why we should be the only
ones who can make a mockery of it.

117
00:09:51,578 --> 00:09:52,879
Protect it through cowardice.

118
00:09:55,461 --> 00:09:57,242
What do you suppose
I should do to train?

119
00:09:58,082 --> 00:10:01,885
Try limiting the mana you release
to one-tenth of its typical volume.

120
00:10:04,967 --> 00:10:05,507
Impressive.

121
00:10:06,247 --> 00:10:07,248
You're controlling it well.

122
00:10:08,961 --> 00:10:11,463
I imagine any elf could
do something so simple.

123
00:10:12,063 --> 00:10:14,445
While you do that, we'll
spend time on fundamentals.

124
00:10:15,126 --> 00:10:16,967
Work to raise the
base of your mana.

125
00:10:17,788 --> 00:10:18,788
Is that really all?

126
00:10:19,569 --> 00:10:20,209
Easy enough.

127
00:10:22,271 --> 00:10:26,274
Do I stop suppressing my mana whenever
I feel like it, or whenever you tell me to?

128
00:10:26,794 --> 00:10:28,936
It'll get tiring if I
do it for too long.

129
00:10:29,556 --> 00:10:31,037
You'll do it for
as long as I have.

130
00:10:32,218 --> 00:10:32,639
For life.

131
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:37,082
If you can, you'll fool Daemonkind
for the rest of your days.

132
00:10:42,782 --> 00:10:44,483
I sense Lord Lügner is dead.

133
00:10:45,464 --> 00:10:47,645
Slaughtered like the
rest of your executioners.

134
00:10:48,305 --> 00:10:50,187
Do you see your failure, Aura?

135
00:10:51,227 --> 00:10:51,868
That I do.

136
00:10:52,208 --> 00:10:53,269
'Tis a shame indeed.

137
00:10:53,949 --> 00:10:57,891
However, if I defeat you here and now,
their sacrifice won't have been for naught.

138
00:10:59,712 --> 00:11:05,796
At the beginning of our skirmish, you made it your priority to
release as many immortal soldiers from my control as you could.

139
00:11:07,217 --> 00:11:08,498
All that work cost you.

140
00:11:08,718 --> 00:11:11,660
Was it wise to expend so much
of your mana right in front of me?

141
00:11:14,770 --> 00:11:16,231
The scales of obedience.

142
00:11:16,952 --> 00:11:22,337
When two souls are placed opposite each other,
whichever has more mana forces the other to submit.

143
00:11:24,038 --> 00:11:28,822
Only someone with as much mana as Aura could
handle this sort of risky magic so casually.

144
00:11:29,903 --> 00:11:34,207
Generally speaking, a person's mana increases
in proportion to time spent training.

145
00:11:36,829 --> 00:11:39,091
I can feel it in the
power pouring off her.

146
00:11:40,071 --> 00:11:46,276
She's a great demon who has lived for over 500 years
and has spent the majority of that time training.

147
00:11:48,838 --> 00:11:49,779
500 years.

148
00:11:50,679 --> 00:11:52,641
That's fairly
long-lived for her kind.

149
00:11:53,621 --> 00:11:55,403
I doubt she's been
challenged before.

150
00:11:56,764 --> 00:11:59,826
I can tell that much from the
mana overflowing from her body.

151
00:12:00,466 --> 00:12:03,989
She has no tricks up her sleeve,
as demons don't conceal their mana.

152
00:12:04,389 --> 00:12:05,350
They can't afford to.

153
00:12:07,272 --> 00:12:08,295
I pity you.

154
00:12:12,230 --> 00:12:13,530
Aselyse.

155
00:12:17,777 --> 00:12:18,177
Master?

156
00:12:20,258 --> 00:12:22,379
Demons are quite cunning
creatures, are they not?

157
00:12:22,879 --> 00:12:26,120
So why haven't they thought to
constantly suppress their mana like you do?

158
00:12:28,141 --> 00:12:29,402
I'm sure they
would if they could.

159
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:37,705
Demons are individualists by nature, but form the frailest
connections needed to stand a chance against humankind.

160
00:12:39,707 --> 00:12:42,029
The barest society
needs what to function?

161
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:44,231
Order, I suppose.

162
00:12:44,712 --> 00:12:45,212
That's right.

163
00:12:46,193 --> 00:12:49,736
Even an organization of monsters
needs someone of importance to lead it.

164
00:12:50,901 --> 00:12:51,962
Humans need the same.

165
00:12:52,342 --> 00:12:54,603
Importance is determined
by status and wealth.

166
00:12:54,884 --> 00:12:57,605
In our world, those who
have both get to rule.

167
00:12:58,446 --> 00:13:00,787
Look at that well-dressed
fellow leaving the palace.

168
00:13:01,247 --> 00:13:02,228
He's clearly important.

169
00:13:03,309 --> 00:13:05,210
But humans have no
innate way of showing that.

170
00:13:05,610 --> 00:13:09,493
So, for others to know he's someone of note,
he has to put on the trappings of rank.

171
00:13:10,153 --> 00:13:11,494
So demons are different, then.

172
00:13:11,937 --> 00:13:16,922
Despite their performance of civilization,
demons haven't changed a bit since beasthood.

173
00:13:17,422 --> 00:13:18,624
Might makes right.

174
00:13:18,984 --> 00:13:20,686
Far more straightforward
than us humans.

175
00:13:21,486 --> 00:13:23,288
You can tell who's
strong by looking at them.

176
00:13:23,949 --> 00:13:24,810
Through their mana?

177
00:13:25,711 --> 00:13:27,572
Mana is everything
to their kind.

178
00:13:28,033 --> 00:13:30,055
Much like status and
wealth are to ours.

179
00:13:30,656 --> 00:13:31,937
It's dignity itself.

180
00:13:33,518 --> 00:13:37,859
Now, there is a chance they may temporarily
suppress their mana for the sake of stealth,

181
00:13:37,883 --> 00:13:42,224
but none are foolish enough to forfeit their
standing to constantly suppress their power.

182
00:13:43,105 --> 00:13:47,426
It's the difference between a noble
sneaking out into town in disguise and

183
00:13:47,450 --> 00:13:51,771
that same noble debasing themselves
by abandoning their station entirely.

184
00:13:52,452 --> 00:13:57,015
Demons know nothing of charity and would
never grant dignity to those with little mana.

185
00:13:57,335 --> 00:13:59,037
Their world is a
cold and cruel one.

186
00:14:00,216 --> 00:14:04,297
So, the stronger an individual is, the
more desperate they are to show it off.

187
00:14:05,337 --> 00:14:09,538
Unlike us, for them there's no benefit
in constantly suppressing their mana.

188
00:14:10,098 --> 00:14:12,379
The thought doesn't so
much as cross their minds.

189
00:14:13,819 --> 00:14:14,960
In a way, I pity them.

190
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:20,361
Just as we are bound by the places we live and the
clothing we can afford, demons are bound by mana.

191
00:14:21,141 --> 00:14:28,103
Magic is the very lifeblood of their species, but for all their
unrivaled love for it, the poor fools can't even control their mana.

192
00:14:29,795 --> 00:14:32,416
Frieren, you're very
lucky you aren't a demon.

193
00:14:33,237 --> 00:14:33,957
I know I am.

194
00:14:34,337 --> 00:14:35,838
I couldn't deceive
them if I were.

195
00:14:35,858 --> 00:14:43,581
It's been three years since you
began suppressing your mana.

196
00:14:44,802 --> 00:14:46,803
I suppose I was right
about you after all.

197
00:14:52,625 --> 00:14:54,146
You've grown
much better at that.

198
00:14:57,323 --> 00:14:59,983
Now tell me, you still
love magic, don't you?

199
00:15:01,444 --> 00:15:03,364
That was rather out
of the blue, Master.

200
00:15:05,024 --> 00:15:06,485
But yes, somewhat.

201
00:15:07,265 --> 00:15:09,125
Your confidence
has waned over time.

202
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:11,866
Long ago, you told me you
loved the craft with fervor.

203
00:15:12,646 --> 00:15:14,446
It's only been fifty
years since then.

204
00:15:15,926 --> 00:15:16,806
A smart girl.

205
00:15:19,607 --> 00:15:23,187
All this time, and the only thing I've
taught my apprentice to do is fight.

206
00:15:24,528 --> 00:15:26,028
Magic fit for revenge.

207
00:15:27,831 --> 00:15:29,091
Is that something you regret?

208
00:15:29,992 --> 00:15:30,532
Not a bit.

209
00:15:31,352 --> 00:15:34,873
No one's better suited to hold on
to the secrets of my magic than you.

210
00:15:35,953 --> 00:15:37,574
You're going to
live a long life.

211
00:15:38,254 --> 00:15:41,334
Perhaps someday you'll become
strong enough to defeat the Demon King.

212
00:15:44,995 --> 00:15:47,296
Frieren, I do have one request.

213
00:15:48,256 --> 00:15:48,756
What is it?

214
00:15:49,617 --> 00:15:52,417
All I ask is that you plant
flowers around my grave.

215
00:15:53,718 --> 00:15:54,918
That doesn't seem like you.

216
00:15:55,270 --> 00:15:55,970
I know.

217
00:15:58,098 --> 00:16:02,223
Frieren, I have a spell that
creates a field of flowers.

218
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:05,127
To tell you the truth, it's
actually my favorite one.

219
00:16:06,688 --> 00:16:08,611
My parents taught it
to me when I was a girl.

220
00:16:09,752 --> 00:16:11,855
It's what made me
fall in love with magic.

221
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:17,742
Then I'd like you
to teach it to me.

222
00:16:26,663 --> 00:16:27,745
Listen to me, Frieren.

223
00:16:28,706 --> 00:16:31,250
You must never seek to
leave your mark on history.

224
00:16:32,192 --> 00:16:33,654
There's safety in obscurity.

225
00:16:35,097 --> 00:16:39,724
And once you've finally defeated the Demon King,
rest assured the whole world shall know your name.

226
00:17:39,878 --> 00:17:42,720
I've heard a seasoned mage
lives somewhere in these woods.

227
00:17:44,461 --> 00:17:45,381
Is that mage you?

228
00:17:46,202 --> 00:17:48,323
Seasoned in the sense
I've been around, perhaps.

229
00:17:48,563 --> 00:17:50,364
But I've done precious
little with my years.

230
00:17:50,384 --> 00:17:53,986
I'm in no way exceptional.

231
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:56,568
What do you think, Heiter?

232
00:17:58,989 --> 00:18:02,151
I would say she has approximately
one-fifth of the mana I do.

233
00:18:02,651 --> 00:18:03,852
Fairly middle of the road.

234
00:18:04,478 --> 00:18:06,018
Way to make a first impression.

235
00:18:06,979 --> 00:18:07,779
Now move along.

236
00:18:08,259 --> 00:18:10,759
You don't have business
with a mediocre mage, do you?

237
00:18:11,279 --> 00:18:15,040
No, but you're easily the strongest
mage I've ever laid eyes on.

238
00:18:16,761 --> 00:18:18,041
And what would
make you say that?

239
00:18:20,021 --> 00:18:24,742
Call it a hunch.

240
00:18:26,543 --> 00:18:27,403
Aselyse.

241
00:18:46,747 --> 00:18:48,668
You seem awfully
happy with yourself.

242
00:18:49,108 --> 00:18:50,869
Are you so certain
you'll win, Aura?

243
00:18:52,729 --> 00:18:54,110
We'll find out soon enough.

244
00:18:55,090 --> 00:18:56,371
Frieren the Slayer.

245
00:18:57,731 --> 00:19:01,693
It's been 80 years since you made your
first meaningful appearance in this world.

246
00:19:02,693 --> 00:19:05,414
With a party of heroes, you
defeated the Demon King.

247
00:19:05,934 --> 00:19:09,296
It makes one wonder just how
long you've had to study your magic.

248
00:19:10,236 --> 00:19:14,678
Unfortunately for you, it matters not how
many years you've managed to survive.

249
00:19:15,444 --> 00:19:18,266
Your mana tells me
everything I need to know.

250
00:19:19,707 --> 00:19:20,948
I can see it clearly.

251
00:19:21,768 --> 00:19:27,152
There is no question you are an exceptional
mage, but your mana itself is unimpressive.

252
00:19:28,072 --> 00:19:31,114
I would wager you've had no
more than a hundred years training.

253
00:19:32,055 --> 00:19:35,377
Not only that, it's been eighty
years and you haven't grown a bit.

254
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:39,120
Were you honing other skills
instead of increasing your mana?

255
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,241
Or were you piddling
your life away?

256
00:19:43,139 --> 00:19:44,340
Just as expected.

257
00:19:44,921 --> 00:19:47,203
You are absolutely
no match for me.

258
00:19:57,592 --> 00:19:58,874
As you can see, I win.

259
00:20:01,616 --> 00:20:05,540
I shall consider it an honor to
sever the head of the Slayer myself.

260
00:20:10,872 --> 00:20:13,954
I'm shocked that it wasn't even
necessary to exhaust her mana.

261
00:20:14,435 --> 00:20:15,936
I needn't have been so cautious.

262
00:20:17,036 --> 00:20:19,879
Though she did defeat a
decent amount of my troops.

263
00:20:21,099 --> 00:20:22,460
I'll have to
replenish them later.

264
00:20:26,663 --> 00:20:27,244
What's this?

265
00:20:28,705 --> 00:20:30,706
The scales are starting
to tip in her direction.

266
00:20:32,368 --> 00:20:35,550
You're the one who opted
to gamble with my soul, Aura.

267
00:20:37,231 --> 00:20:41,474
To tell you the truth, I would have been in real
trouble if you had tried to overwhelm me with numbers.

268
00:20:42,214 --> 00:20:45,176
I'm grateful for your overconfidence
when it comes to your mana.

269
00:20:46,397 --> 00:20:48,138
Now I can finally defeat you.

270
00:20:49,419 --> 00:20:50,359
Oh, can you now?

271
00:20:51,220 --> 00:20:52,741
You really should
have figured it out.

272
00:20:53,721 --> 00:20:55,222
I've been suppressing my mana.

273
00:20:56,203 --> 00:20:59,145
A grave miscalculation
on your part, Aura.

274
00:21:01,780 --> 00:21:06,101
Valiant last-ditch effort, but there's no
chance that could have escaped my notice.

275
00:21:06,801 --> 00:21:12,022
There wasn't a hint of the instability or variation
in your mana output that comes with suppression.

276
00:21:13,183 --> 00:21:14,023
I'm surprised.

277
00:21:14,543 --> 00:21:17,643
Demons are capable of
observing mana with such accuracy.

278
00:21:18,944 --> 00:21:21,524
Seems my master was
right in her methods after all.

279
00:21:22,745 --> 00:21:26,425
I've spent the better part of my life
in a constant state of suppression.

280
00:21:27,386 --> 00:21:28,926
It has become natural for me.

281
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:32,318
You're dimmer than I thought.

282
00:21:32,699 --> 00:21:34,879
Why would you ever
do something so foolish?

283
00:21:35,399 --> 00:21:36,220
Foolish, yes.

284
00:21:36,860 --> 00:21:37,660
But powerful.

285
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,641
It lets me defeat your kind.

286
00:21:44,482 --> 00:21:45,322
This is absurd!

287
00:21:46,623 --> 00:21:49,484
I'm a great demon who
has lived for over 500 years!

288
00:21:51,724 --> 00:22:00,327
Aura, the one standing before you, is a
great mage who's lived for over a thousand.

289
00:22:14,670 --> 00:22:24,132
Frieren, just as demons deceive mankind with
their words, you must deceive them with your mana.

290
00:22:24,813 --> 00:22:28,614
Aura, kill yourself.

291
00:22:36,235 --> 00:22:42,217
This can't be... No...
How could I ever...

